  "texts": [
    "In this context, Confidential Computing (CC) (Sardar and Fetzer 2023) is built on the basis of hardware-assisted TEE and focuses on protecting data during processing.",
    "CC also provides remote attestation that enables users to verify the integrity and confidentiality of code and data in the execution environment.",
    "SEE in CC is often implemented as virtual machines that reduce the surface of attacks, simplify implementation, and allow users to execute native codes in CC without modification.",
    "The confidential container (Yang et al. 2021) is defined by the Cloud Native Computing Foundation (CNCF) as an open source project aiming to standardize confidential computing at the container level and simplify its consumption in Kubernetes.",
    "FL democratizes data-driven insights by training ML models on distributed data without sharing sensitive data across devices or servers."
  ],
